  "text": "It has recently been shown that PEPCK, one of the key enzymes regulating gluconeogenesis, alone only has a weak influence during this process [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . In our Arx-deficient animals, we found reduced expression of genes regulating hepatic gluconeogenesis, including a 60% reduction in the PEPCK protein levels. Burgess et al. [CITATION_3] showed that the protein levels of PEPCK have to be reduced by 80% or more before any effects are observed. However, the lack of glucagon in our mice impacts the expression of several gluconeogenic genes other than PEPCK, which likely collectively affect glucose production.",
